title: Tresor By Lancome For Women. Deodorant Spray 3.4 Ounces
description: Introduced in 1990. Fragrance notes: lilac and apricot, with lower notes with amber and musk. Recommended use: casual.When applying any fragrance please consider that there are several factors which can affect the natural smell of your skin and, in turn, the way a scent smells on you.  For instance, your mood, stress level, age, body chemistry, diet, and current medications may all alter the scents you wear.  Similarly, factor such as dry or oily skin can even affect the amount of time a fragrance will last after being applied

title: Tropic Isle Living Jamaican Black Castor Oil, 4 Ounce
description: Tropic isle's living jamaican black castor oil is a rich, light brown oil which is processed the old fashioned way by roasting the castor bean. Jamaican black castor oil origin can be traced back to  ethiopia, africa. It's believed that this natural castor oil originally came to jamaica from slaves taken from africa. Jamaican elders didn't waste any time in discovering the various uses for this oil. Black castor oil is a great addition to any hair or skincare regimen. This castor oil can be use as is or add to your favorite hair products.

title: New Essie Spring 2013 Collection Madison Ave-Hue 821 Madison Ave-Hue
description: Essie Madison Ave-Hue Spring Collection for 2013 is inspired by the large cities like New York, London, Paris, Munich, Rio and Tokyo. Essie Weingarten, founder and global creative director for essie, finds its inspiration from several cities. - You can not just select a city, then it is their differences that make them so special, says Essie. The collection will give sensation of the biggest shopping cities in the world, and sure feels Hip-Anema much of Rio de Janeiro!
